Pre-Game Insights: The Pearl Divers (Bahrain) have had inconsistent results in recent international matches, often winning against weaker opponents but struggling against stronger ones.
Bahrain aims to show consistent performance ahead of the AFC Asian Cup 2024, where they face challenging groups including South Korea, Jordan, and Malaysia.
Australia, led by Graham Arnold, will field a mix of experienced and young players, aiming to maintain their status as favorites after winning the 2015 Asian Cup.
Samuel Silvera, a 23-year-old striker, is expected to play a key role for Australia in the upcoming Asian Cup.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The match will take place at Stadion Baniyas, Abu Dhabi, on January 6, 2024, at 21:00 WIB.
Bahrain is ranked 86th in FIFA standings, while Australia is ranked 25th.
This will be Bahrain's 7th participation in the final stage of the Asian Cup, with their best performance being reaching the semifinals in 2019.
Australia will play against Bahrain as part of their preparation for the 2024 Asian Cup, which is their last warm-up match before the tournament.
